<p>
A <a href="/docs/Fields">field</a> implementing the Email <a href="/docs/Field_Types">field type</a> can store a value as string that conforms to the format <code>user@domain.extension</code>.
</p>

<p>
The Email <a href="/docs/Field_Types">field type</a> has two optional parameters named <code>Domain</code> and <code>Prefix</code> that can be used to restrict the acceptable addresses.
</p>

<div class="heading">Example Field</div>
<pre>{
	"Name" : "My Email Field",
	"Field Type" : "Email",
	"Description" : "The example usage of the Email Field Type.",
	"Required" : true,
	"Parameters" : {
		"Domain" : "minocloud.com",//OPTIONAL
		"Prefix" : "app_"//OPTIONAL
	} 
}</pre>


<div class="heading">Example Value</div>
<pre>"ExampleUser.MyType.1" : {
	...
	"My Email Field" : "app_example@minocloud.com",
	...
}</pre>